---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="TradeStudio vs TradingView, TrendSpider, Thinkorswim — Comparison" description="See how TradeStudio compares to TradingView, TrendSpider, Thinkorswim, and QuantConnect on AI depth, charting, backtesting, scripting, and price.">

  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold md:text-5xl">How TradeStudio compares</h1>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-secondary">We respect the tools you use. Here's an honest look at where TradeStudio fits — and where it leads.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Full Comparison Matrix -->
  <section class="border-t border-border bg-bg-secondary py-16 px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-bold">Feature comparison</h2>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-primary p-6">
        <ComparisonTable />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Individual Comparisons -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6" id="tradingview">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-secondary p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">TradeStudio vs TradingView</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          TradingView has 100M users and the best community in trading. Its charts are beautiful and Pine Script is well-documented. We're not trying to replace it for social trading or quick chart sharing.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          TradeStudio is for traders who've outgrown Pine Script. If you want AI to generate real C# strategies, compile them live, and backtest them — all from a natural language prompt — that's what we built. TradingView doesn't generate code. It doesn't backtest AI earnings predictions. And it runs in a browser, not a native desktop app.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent-green">Where TradeStudio leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>AI strategy generation (NL → C# → backtest)</li>
              <li>AI earnings narrative backtest</li>
              <li>Desktop performance (native WPF)</li>
              <li>C# scripting via Roslyn</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-secondary">Where TradingView leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Community and social features</li>
              <li>Pine Script ecosystem</li>
              <li>Cross-platform (web)</li>
              <li>Market coverage breadth</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6" id="trendspider">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-secondary p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">TradeStudio vs TrendSpider</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          TrendSpider is the closest competitor. They have AI chat, automated pattern recognition, and no-code strategy building. They're a solid product — and at $52–155/month, they charge accordingly.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          The difference: TrendSpider's AI generates no-code strategies. TradeStudio generates real C# code, compiles it live via Roslyn, and lets you read, modify, and extend every line. We also offer earnings and narrative backtests that TrendSpider simply doesn't have. If you want code-level control with AI-level convenience, that's the gap we fill.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent-green">Where TradeStudio leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Real C# code generation (not no-code)</li>
              <li>Earnings narrative backtest (unique)</li>
              <li>Roslyn in-process compilation</li>
              <li>Desktop performance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-secondary">Where TrendSpider leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Automated pattern recognition</li>
              <li>No-code accessibility</li>
              <li>Multi-timeframe analysis</li>
              <li>Established user base</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6" id="thinkorswim">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-secondary p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">TradeStudio vs Thinkorswim</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Thinkorswim is free with a Schwab account and has excellent charting. For traders who just need charts and options analysis, it's hard to beat free.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          But ToS has zero AI strategy generation. thinkScript is capable but limited compared to C#. If you want AI as a first-class research tool — not a bolted-on chatbot — TradeStudio is the answer. We built AI into the core workflow, not the sidebar.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent-green">Where TradeStudio leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>AI strategy generation</li>
              <li>AI earnings & narrative backtests</li>
              <li>C# scripting (vs thinkScript)</li>
              <li>AI-first architecture</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-secondary">Where Thinkorswim leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Free (with Schwab account)</li>
              <li>Options analysis tools</li>
              <li>Paper trading</li>
              <li>Broker integration</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 pb-16" id="quantconnect">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-secondary p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">TradeStudio vs QuantConnect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          QuantConnect is built for quants who write code. It's powerful, well-documented, and supports multiple languages. If you're a developer who loves writing backtests from scratch, it's excellent.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          TradeStudio is for traders who want code-level power from natural language. Same rigor — real compiled code, real metrics — but you describe what you want instead of writing boilerplate. The Strategy Lab lets you go from idea to backtest in 30 seconds, not 30 minutes.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-accent-green">Where TradeStudio leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Natural language → compiled code</li>
              <li>30-second idea-to-backtest</li>
              <li>AI earnings/narrative backtests</li>
              <li>Built-in charting (SkiaSharp)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-bg-tertiary p-4">
            <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-secondary">Where QuantConnect leads</h4>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-text-secondary">
              <li>Multi-language support</li>
              <li>Cloud backtesting at scale</li>
              <li>Live trading integration</li>
              <li>Research notebooks</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Ready to see the difference?"
    subtitle="Download TradeStudio and test a strategy in under a minute."
    primaryCta={{ label: 'Download for Windows', href: '/download' }}
  />

</BaseLayout>
